scripts/refresh_rrc_drilling_permits.py (390 lines):
  - Multi-segment record dispatcher keyed on bytes 1-2 (RRC-TAPE-RECORD-ID).
  - DAROOT (01): primary key + county + lease + district + operator + status
    flag + permit_no + issue_date. Permian-county filter + status='A'
    (Approved) filter applied at this stage to bound memory.
  - DAPERMIT (02): handles documented 4-byte header anomaly per oga049m
    p.II.13. Yields well_number, total_depth, type-application code,
    issued_date.
  - DAW999A1 (14): GIS surface coords. PIC 9(5)V9(7) implied-decimal parser.
    Source longitude is positive — sign-flipped on parse for Texas (W of
    Greenwich). Two join paths: (1) explicit primary-key field at trailing
    bytes 27-35 if present, (2) positional fallback to most-recent
    Permian-Approved root per oga049m segment hierarchy (page I.2 tree).
  - NAD27 → WGS84 via pyproj.Transformer(EPSG:4267, EPSG:4326). ~52m offset
    in the Permian basin. Repo convention is WGS84 per ARCHITECTURE.md §76.
  - 11 Permian counties hardcoded by RRC code: PECOS=371, REEVES=389,
    WARD=475, LOVING=301, WINKLER=495, CULBERSON=109, CRANE=103, UPTON=461,
    REAGAN=383, CROCKETT=105, TERRELL=443. Same set as scrape_rrc_w1.py.
  - 15 type-application codes mapped to human labels (oga049m II.16).
  - Output: combined_points.csv 31-column canonical schema, layer_id=
    drilling_permits, atomic temp+os.replace per §6.15.

scripts/test_refresh_drilling_permits_smoke.py (175 lines):
